@* A FRAGMENT FORWARDED TWO LEVELS (decision 168, register defect A7). Fwd.razor renders
   <FwdInner>@ChildContent</FwdInner>, so this parent's span has to travel through TWO composition
   boundaries before anything places it.

   BEFORE #168 IT WAS DROPPED IN TOTAL SILENCE: emitting a fragment CLEARED the slot map before
   walking its nodes, so Fwd's own @ChildContent resolved against nothing. Exit 0, no diagnostic, the
   span simply absent and #inner empty. The map to consult inside a fragment is the one in scope
   where that fragment was WRITTEN -- for Fwd's content, this file's. *@
<div id="wrap"><Fwd><span id="body">@count</span></Fwd><button id="inc" @onclick="Inc">inc</button></div>

@code {
    private int count = 0;
    void Inc() { count++; }
}
